Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.34,0:00:06.33,Default,>> Stanford University.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.79,0:00:12.07,Default,>> Okay. Well, welcome\Nto lecture number 18
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.07,0:00:15.32,Default,of CS193P, fall 2013/14.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.87,0:00:18.43,Default,Before I talk about what I'm\Ngoing to talk about today,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.43,0:00:20.13,Default,let's talk a little\Nbit about what's coming
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.13,0:00:22.38,Default,up because we're right at\Nthe end of the quarter here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.75,0:00:25.28,Default,So on Wednesday --\Nnext lecture --
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.39,0:00:27.15,Default,we are going to have\Nthis alternate final
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.15,0:00:28.29,Default,presentation day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.59,0:00:32.30,Default,And a few of you have already\Nsaid that you wanted to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.30,0:00:34.97,Default,And really, the only thing you\Nneed to do to sign up to do
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.97,0:00:37.96,Default,that if you want to use\Nthis Wednesday as opposed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.96,0:00:41.81,Default,to the following Thursday\Nnormal final presentation time
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.81,0:00:45.89,Default,to do your presentation, is\Nto submit the Keynote slides,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.23,0:00:48.17,Default,okay, by tomorrow at noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.37,0:00:49.00,Default,That's very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.00,0:00:50.77,Default,If I don't see your\Nslides by tomorrow at noon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.80,0:00:52.90,Default,then you're basically not going\Nto be presenting on Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.90,0:00:57.40,Default,And then you'll be forced\Nto present next Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.14,0:01:01.18,Default,So the only thing I'll say\Nabout your Keynote slides,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.37,0:01:03.73,Default,make sure that they're\Nwidescreen format,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.89,0:01:06.68,Default,okay, 1280 by 720.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.84,0:01:10.22,Default,If you are submitting PowerPoint\Nor something else, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.22,0:01:11.68,Default,you're taking your\Nchances because I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.68,0:01:12.81,Default,to convert them to Keynote.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.03,0:01:15.70,Default,So if they have fonts and\Nstuff, convert them --
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.70,0:01:17.48,Default,you're in good shape;\Nif not, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.60,0:01:21.29,Default,you're slides might\Nlook a little wonky.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.29,0:01:22.89,Default,You just submit them\Nnormally, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:25.16,Default,Just do the normal\Nclass submit script.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.92,0:01:28.02,Default,You submit it as\Nyour final project.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.02,0:01:29.36,Default,And of course, you\Ncan submit again,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.82,0:01:30.99,Default,all the way up until\Nthe deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.99,0:01:33.84,Default,And the other thing we're\Ngoing to do on Wednesday
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.84,0:01:36.80,Default,after we have a few\Npeople, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.80,0:01:39.72,Default,do their final presentations --\Nwhich by the way, I, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.72,0:01:42.62,Default,really encourage all of you\Nto come and be an audience
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.62,0:01:46.11,Default,for those people just\Nbecause you'll get
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.11,0:01:48.14,Default,to see some final presentations;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.14,0:01:49.19,Default,you'll get a little\Nbit of bonus.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.19,0:01:52.43,Default,I'll talk a little bit about\Nthe final presentations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.94,0:01:55.24,Default,If I see something, I'm\Nlike, "Oh, let's make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.24,0:01:57.96,Default,that this doesn't happen\Nnext Thursday or whatever."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.32,0:02:01.46,Default,Also, after that's\Ndone, if you're planning
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.46,0:02:03.89,Default,to do a live demo,\NWednesday will be a great time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.89,0:02:05.44,Default,because I'll have\Nthis whole setup here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.44,0:02:07.32,Default,And you can try and\Nhook up your device,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.32,0:02:09.84,Default,and using this wireless\Nthing that I use,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.19,0:02:15.40,Default,and this thing right here --\Nwhich let me set that up --
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.75,0:02:18.77,Default,to show your demo and make\Nsure that it's working,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.77,0:02:21.02,Default,make sure your device\Nworks, all that stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.07,0:02:22.67,Default,so that you can have\Na nice, smooth demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.67,0:02:24.57,Default,Okay? So we'll be doing\Nall that on Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.91,0:02:28.56,Default,Otherwise I'm not going to\Npresent a particular topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.86,0:02:32.63,Default,So it's one of those things\Nwhere, again, I encourage you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.63,0:02:34.42,Default,to come be an audience\Nfor the people
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.42,0:02:36.33,Default,who are doing alternate\Npresentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.33,0:02:37.62,Default,but it's not a mandatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.90,0:02:38.88,Default,I mean, all these lectures
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.88,0:02:41.05,Default,at the end here are\Nnot mandatory per se.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.65,0:02:43.64,Default,But that's what's\Ngoing on, on Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.09,0:02:46.42,Default,Okay? Any questions about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.87,0:02:47.35,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:49.67,Default,And then Friday, no\Nsection on Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.67,0:02:51.57,Default,I think it might even\Nbe officially start
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.57,0:02:53.16,Default,of final exam period on Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.16,0:02:54.06,Default,I'm not one hundred\Npercent sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:55.39,Default,But in any case, no section.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.85,0:02:58.62,Default,We've moved your project\Ndeadline, as you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.62,0:03:00.17,Default,to Sunday night at midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.69,0:03:04.49,Default,And when you submit your final\Nproject, submit your slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.58,0:03:06.40,Default,Okay? Assuming you're\Nnot submitting them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.40,0:03:09.39,Default,by noon tomorrow, make sure you\Nsubmit them by Sunday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.39,0:03:11.07,Default,And just put them\Nright at the top level
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.13,0:03:12.06,Default,of whatever you submit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.06,0:03:13.51,Default,Just whatever the top\Nlevel directory is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.51,0:03:15.07,Default,just put them there\N-- Keynote slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.07,0:03:19.86,Default,The final presentations\Nare a week from Thursday,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.86,0:03:21.75,Default,so the normally scheduled\Nfinal exam period
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.75,0:03:23.81,Default,for this class, 12:15 to 3:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.23,0:03:25.47,Default,The presentation is required.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.47,0:03:26.64,Default,Some people say,\N"Is it optional?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.64,0:03:27.39,Default,No, it's required.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.96,0:03:30.24,Default,You get two and a half\Nminutes this quarter,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.24,0:03:31.14,Default,which is a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.14,0:03:33.55,Default,Usually we only give\Ntwo minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.55,0:03:35.51,Default,And seems like a long\Ntime; when you get
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.51,0:03:36.77,Default,up there it will seem short.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:39.85,Default,And again, widescreen\Naspect ratio.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.85,0:03:41.66,Default,And the order is\Ngoing to be random.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.66,0:03:44.11,Default,You're not going to find out\Nuntil the day you get it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.11,0:03:46.93,Default,so don't even send me something\Nthat I says, "Oh, I got a flight
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.93,0:03:48.69,Default,to catch, so let me go first."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.69,0:03:50.01,Default,Okay? If you got\Na flight to catch,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.01,0:03:51.77,Default,then go on Wednesday, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.85,0:03:55.18,Default,Go the day after tomorrow\Nbecause for fairness,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.18,0:03:56.68,Default,I'm going to put it\Nin a random order
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:03:58.15,Default,that will be revealed\Nat the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.55,0:04:01.91,Default,Okay? Any questions about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.46,0:04:03.12,Default,We're about to find --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.12,0:04:06.45,Default,any questions about the final\Nproject submission process
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.45,0:04:08.25,Default,or due date Sunday night?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.24,0:04:10.41,Default,Okay. Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.84,0:04:14.05,Default,So today's two topics,\Nlocalization --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.05,0:04:15.66,Default,really, it's\Ninternationalization
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.66,0:04:16.56,Default,that I'm going to\Nbe talking about --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:18.91,Default,and then settings,\Nwhich is a UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.20,0:04:22.16,Default,You can add UI to the\Nsettings application
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.00,0:04:25.43,Default,to control certain settings\Nabout your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:26.88,Default,And the two demos\NI'm going to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.88,0:04:30.22,Default,I'm going to internationalize\NPhotoMania, and I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.22,0:04:31.69,Default,to add a setting to Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.69,0:04:33.89,Default,Okay? That way we'll get\Nboth of these things demoed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.43,0:04:34.65,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.65,0:04:36.25,Default,So let's talk about\Ninternationalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.25,0:04:38.43,Default,There's really two steps\Nto internationalization:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.66,0:04:40.63,Default,There's something we called\N"internationalization" --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.88,0:04:44.24,Default,sometimes abbreviated I-18-N\Nbecause there's 18 letters
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.24,0:04:45.94,Default,in there; I-18-N,\Ninternationalization --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.23,0:04:47.72,Default,and then there's localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.01,0:04:50.09,Default,"Internationalization"\Nis the process
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.09,0:04:53.46,Default,of making your app\Npossible to be localized.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.46,0:04:56.84,Default,Okay? Making it so that\Nyour app can be shipped
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.84,0:04:58.66,Default,in multiple different languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.90,0:05:02.27,Default,"Localization" is the process\Nof actually translating that --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.51,0:05:04.76,Default,your application -- to\Nanother language, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.76,0:05:05.84,Default,So it's really a\Ntwo-step process.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.84,0:05:06.66,Default,Internationalization,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:08.25,Default,that's something you\Ndo as the developer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.61,0:05:11.05,Default,Localization, usually hire\Nsomeone to go do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.59,0:05:14.50,Default,I don't recommend using Google\NTranslate to localize your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:15.95,Default,You get some very\Nstrange results.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.95,0:05:17.98,Default,You want a professional\Nlocalizer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:22.98,Default,who understands the idioms\Nof the local language.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.11,0:05:25.86,Default,There's really two things\Nthat need to be localized:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.86,0:05:28.69,Default,One is your storyboard\Nand one is kind
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.69,0:05:30.47,Default,of all the literal strings\Nin your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.47,0:05:32.22,Default,So let's talk about\Nthe storyboards first.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.53,0:05:34.52,Default,The way we localize storyboards
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.52,0:05:39.48,Default,in iOS 7 is we only change\Nthe strings that appear
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.73,0:05:42.68,Default,in the storyboard, and we\Nlet Auto Layout resize things
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.68,0:05:45.04,Default,to fit wider and\Nshorter strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:48.94,Default,Okay? That's a great side\Nbenefit of having Auto Layout,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.94,0:05:51.22,Default,is that localization now\Nis just about the strings
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.22,0:05:52.30,Default,when it comes to the storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.92,0:05:53.94,Default,But the first thing we need
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:57.85,Default,to do before we do any\Nlocalization is to go
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.85,0:06:02.21,Default,to our project settings and set\Nthe list of all the languages
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.21,0:06:04.57,Default,that we are going to\Nsupport localization for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.97,0:06:07.52,Default,Okay? So you know, as\Nyou release new versions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.52,0:06:09.21,Default,of your app, you'll support\Na few more languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.21,0:06:12.35,Default,You'll go back to this project\Nsettings and add more languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.69,0:06:15.24,Default,One thing that's a little\Ntricky about this is you're used
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.24,0:06:16.51,Default,to going to your\Nproject settings,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:19.31,Default,which is that upper left-hand\Ntop part of the navigator.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.59,0:06:22.07,Default,But actually, what we've\Nbeen setting the settings
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.07,0:06:25.47,Default,of there is the target, the\Napp that you're building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.67,0:06:27.14,Default,Here you want to\Nactually set the settings
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.18,0:06:28.72,Default,of the project itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.72,0:06:31.38,Default,So you can see where\Nthat little bubble points
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.38,0:06:32.97,Default,to right there that\Nsays PhotoMania.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.36,0:06:35.65,Default,That's a little popup actually;\Nyou're going to click that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.65,0:06:37.66,Default,and switch up to\Nediting the project.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.66,0:06:39.17,Default,And when you do, there's\Nnot a whole lot of settings
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.17,0:06:40.11,Default,for the whole project.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.11,0:06:42.19,Default,You're seeing them\Nall right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.51,0:06:44.15,Default,And you're just going to go\Ndown to the bottom there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.15,0:06:45.16,Default,It says localizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.16,0:06:47.05,Default,It's just a list of languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:49.76,Default,These are pre-supported\Nlanguages
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.76,0:06:52.07,Default,because these languages need\Nto match up with the languages
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.07,0:06:55.89,Default,that the operating system, iOS,\Nsupports so that when people go
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.89,0:06:57.74,Default,to settings and other apps,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.82,0:07:00.00,Default,that's in whatever\Nlanguage as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.23,0:07:01.66,Default,So when you hit that\Nlittle plus button
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.66,0:07:04.00,Default,down in the lower left-hand\Ncorner, it's going to be a popup
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.00,0:07:04.96,Default,with a list of languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.96,0:07:08.39,Default,You're not going to just type\Nin the word Arabic or French;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.46,0:07:11.43,Default,it's going to be something\Nyou're going to pick from a list
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.43,0:07:13.40,Default,of supported languages for iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.85,0:07:15.42,Default,And you can also see
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.42,0:07:18.05,Default,that there's a language\Nthere called base, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.05,0:07:21.29,Default,And there's a switch that says\Nuse base internationalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:23.95,Default,The concept of base\Ninternationalization is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.95,0:07:26.60,Default,that there's going\Nto be a localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.60,0:07:29.63,Default,It's not a localization that\Nis in anybody's language;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.63,0:07:30.97,Default,it's just the base localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.17,0:07:33.16,Default,And that's going to be kind\Nof like all the defaults:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.38,0:07:35.99,Default,The default storyboard strings,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.99,0:07:38.62,Default,default strings throughout\Nyour app are going to come
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.62,0:07:39.97,Default,out of the base localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.33,0:07:41.91,Default,And then all these\Nother localizations,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.91,0:07:45.81,Default,like English even, but French,\Nand German, and whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.06,0:07:48.79,Default,those are going to\Nmodify those strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.79,0:07:50.87,Default,And so if you forget\Nto localize a string,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.05,0:07:54.49,Default,the base localization\Nwill shine through, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.11,0:07:56.65,Default,And so we'll see what that\Nlooks like when it comes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.65,0:07:59.40,Default,to storyboards in a second here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.52,0:08:03.03,Default,So the storyboards\Nlook like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.31,0:08:05.04,Default,You select a storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.14,0:08:08.40,Default,And when you do the\Nthing I showed you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.71,0:08:11.62,Default,on the previous slide, then your\Nstoryboards are going to look
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.62,0:08:12.92,Default,like this in the file navigator.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.92,0:08:15.11,Default,You see how there's\Nmain, iPhone, storyboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.31,0:08:18.91,Default,And now it has a little\Ntriangle that you can click
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.95,0:08:21.34,Default,and it now is showing\Nunderneath it main, iPhone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.34,0:08:23.19,Default,storyboard again -- base.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.29,0:08:25.24,Default,So that's your base storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.56,0:08:28.62,Default,And then for French, it says\Nmain, iPhone, dot strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.95,0:08:31.82,Default,So that's just the strings\Nonly for the storyboards
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.82,0:08:33.57,Default,that have been extracted, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.76,0:08:36.82,Default,When we did that previous thing,\Nit extracted those out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.16,0:08:38.87,Default,And when you click on the\Nstoryboard and if you go
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:41.81,Default,to the file inspector, you can\Nsee this little thing showing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.81,0:08:44.70,Default,there where there's base --\Nthere will always be base --
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.95,0:08:48.44,Default,and then however many languages\Nyou want to translate to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:50.52,Default,Now, here notice that\NEnglish is not even checked;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.79,0:08:54.55,Default,that's because I'm going to\Nassume that my base is English.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.10,0:08:57.39,Default,Okay? Now, you don't\Nalways want to assume that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.39,0:08:59.24,Default,And you could even\Nmostly assume that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.24,0:09:01.07,Default,but still have an\NEnglish dot strings file
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.07,0:09:03.05,Default,that changed a couple\Nof things if you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.50,0:09:06.82,Default,Or you could have the\Nwhole thing be, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.01,0:09:09.29,Default,explicitly in a strings\Nfile for English.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.70,0:09:12.03,Default,But here I have not\Neven checked English.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:14.19,Default,So whatever's in my base\Nstoryboard, that's what's going
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.19,0:09:15.83,Default,to ship when I'm in\Nthe language English.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.83,0:09:17.57,Default,But in French I have\Na localizable
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.57,0:09:19.54,Default,without strings file, which\NI'll show you in a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.85,0:09:22.70,Default,which is going to change all\Nthe strings in my storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:26.53,Default,So what does that look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.34,0:09:29.05,Default,The French language strings?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.43,0:09:31.84,Default,I'm going to postpone\Nshowing what that looks
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.84,0:09:33.75,Default,like until we talk about\Nstrings in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.90,0:09:37.58,Default,And so let's talk\Nabout literal strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.61,0:09:40.09,Default,So the storyboard\Nstrings are going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.09,0:09:42.48,Default,in this thing I showed\Nyou in the last slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.82,0:09:44.95,Default,But there's other strings\Ninside your app that aren't
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.95,0:09:46.50,Default,in the storyboard,\Nlike things that come
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.50,0:09:48.62,Default,up in alert messages,\Nthe alert buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.62,0:09:51.04,Default,All those things are\Nnot in your storyboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.04,0:09:52.54,Default,but they need be\Nlocalized as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.54,0:09:54.51,Default,And the way we get those strings
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.51,0:09:57.66,Default,to be localizable is using\Nthese macros here that start
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.66,0:09:59.93,Default,with NS localized string.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.06,0:10:01.92,Default,So there's NS localized\Nstring with default value;
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.92,0:10:03.72,Default,there's NS localized\Nstring from table;
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.72,0:10:05.13,Default,there's NS localized string.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:07.95,Default,And each of these macros takes a\Nlittle bit different arguments.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.95,0:10:11.21,Default,But the main thing they're doing\Nis you're giving a key that's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.21,0:10:12.85,Default,going to be looked\Nup in a strings file
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.85,0:10:14.15,Default,and it's going to\Nreturn a value.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.48,0:10:16.17,Default,The different variants\Njust determine:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.17,0:10:18.42,Default,What's the default value\Nif I can't find the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.42,0:10:21.17,Default,in the string, and which\Ndot strings file am I going
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.17,0:10:21.73,Default,to look in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.17,0:10:24.28,Default,Okay, for our storyboard\Nthere's always one string
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.28,0:10:25.06,Default,file associated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.41,0:10:29.74,Default,But when we have literal strings\Ninside of our code, we can split
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.82,0:10:33.93,Default,up all the translations into\Ndifferent files if we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.93,0:10:35.05,Default,In the demo I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.05,0:10:36.85,Default,I'll put them in a\Nlittle separate file just
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.85,0:10:37.88,Default,for one view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.49,0:10:43.20,Default,So for example, if you had the\Nliteral string hello, at sign,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.20,0:10:45.74,Default,quote, hello in your app\Nand that is going to appear
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.74,0:10:47.18,Default,in the UI, then you would change
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.18,0:10:51.24,Default,that to NS localized\Nstring at hello comma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.38,0:10:54.07,Default,And then, the last\Nargument there is a comment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.17,0:10:56.22,Default,to the localizers, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.47,0:10:59.23,Default,So you can assume the\Nlocalizers speak your language,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.41,0:11:00.76,Default,whatever your base language is,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.19,0:11:02.81,Default,and you're giving\Nthem a comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.81,0:11:04.58,Default,You're telling them\Nwhat is this hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.75,0:11:05.42,Default,Where does it appear?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.42,0:11:06.66,Default,What's its environment?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.66,0:11:07.94,Default,So here I'm saying\Nit's a greeting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.94,0:11:09.16,Default,at the start of the application.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.16,0:11:11.13,Default,So the person would\Nknow in French to make
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.13,0:11:12.98,Default,that be bonjour or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.13,0:11:16.96,Default,Right? So that's how you\Nchange all your literal strings
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.96,0:11:19.72,Default,to these NS localized\Nstring, one of these variants.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.21,0:11:21.78,Default,Now what are these\Nthings actually doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.78,0:11:22.94,Default,these NS localized string?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.33,0:11:25.83,Default,They're actually calling\Na method in NS bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.42,0:11:31.16,Default,Okay? NS bundle is a class that\Nkind of collects everything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.16,0:11:33.90,Default,about your app, okay,\Ninto an API
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.11,0:11:35.74,Default,for accessing the\Nresources of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.02,0:11:38.19,Default,And we can use it to\Naccess strings files,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.19,0:11:39.70,Default,and we do that with this method
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.70,0:11:41.02,Default,in bundle called\Nlocalized string
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.02,0:11:43.41,Default,for key value table, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.41,0:11:46.05,Default,Exactly what you would think:\NKey is what we're looking
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.05,0:11:48.42,Default,up in the strings files;\Nvalue is the default there;
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.42,0:11:50.80,Default,and table is which\Ntable to look in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.14,0:11:54.65,Default,The bundle can also be used,\Nby the way, to find URLs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.73,0:11:57.28,Default,to resources like\Nimages, things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.28,0:11:59.99,Default,If you drag an image\N-- a JPEG image --
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.99,0:12:02.42,Default,right into the top\Nlevel of your navigator,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.56,0:12:04.64,Default,then you can use NS\Nbundle main bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.81,0:12:07.31,Default,There's something\Ncalled URL for resource,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.61,0:12:09.45,Default,and you give it the\Nname of that JPEG file.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.45,0:12:10.66,Default,It will give you a URL to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.97,0:12:13.14,Default,Sometimes you need a\Nfull URL to some image.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.14,0:12:15.73,Default,Or if you're not using image\Nnamed, you need some full URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.73,0:12:18.57,Default,So NS bundle is a\Nclass for you to kind
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.19,0:12:21.10,Default,of understand a little\Nbit as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.67,0:12:22.66,Default,But we don't usually --
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.66,0:12:25.45,Default,well, sometimes we'll call\Nthis localized string for key,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.45,0:12:26.62,Default,and I'll do it in\Nthe demo as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.62,0:12:29.85,Default,But we can use the\Nmacros, we should.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.93,0:12:32.08,Default,But there's a significant\Nlimitation on those macros,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.08,0:12:34.99,Default,the NS localized string:\NAll the arguments have
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.05,0:12:39.78,Default,to be literal strings, including\Nthe comment; the key; the value;
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.78,0:12:42.87,Default,the table name; etc.\NThey can't be variables.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.87,0:12:44.13,Default,They have to be literal things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.18,0:12:45.90,Default,At sign quote something,\Nat sign quote something
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.90,0:12:48.37,Default,for every argument of\Nthose localized strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.37,0:12:49.95,Default,And then let's talk\Nabout why that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.43,0:12:54.61,Default,The answer for that is there's\Na command line utility called
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.61,0:12:57.12,Default,genstrings -- short\Nfor generate strings --
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.55,0:12:59.93,Default,which will look through\Na dot M file
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.14,0:13:02.83,Default,for all those NS\Nlocalized string macros
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.03,0:13:06.02,Default,and extract them all out\Ninto a strings file for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.62,0:13:10.21,Default,Okay? And that's how you\Nget the base string file
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.35,0:13:12.22,Default,that you will then\Nlocalize to other languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.89,0:13:14.76,Default,Okay? And we'll show\Nthis in the demo as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.17,0:13:17.39,Default,And so, for example, we had\Nthat NS localized string
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.39,0:13:19.45,Default,at sign hello, greeting\Nat start of application.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.69,0:13:22.33,Default,That would get turned into\Nthe following two lines there
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:25.36,Default,in a strings file:\NComment, greeting is started
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.36,0:13:27.67,Default,by application, and\Nthen hello equals hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.06,0:13:30.27,Default,And the French person\Nwould come along
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.27,0:13:32.93,Default,and they would change\Nhello equals bonjour.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.48,0:13:35.88,Default,Now, when you do genstrings
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.88,0:13:37.90,Default,and you get dot strings\Nfiles generated --
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:39.65,Default,and you might get multiple\Nof them because remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.65,0:13:42.79,Default,one of the NS localized\Nstrings is NS localized string
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.79,0:13:44.66,Default,from table, so you might\Nspecify table name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.66,0:13:46.73,Default,And so it might be making\Nmultiple dot strings files
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.73,0:13:47.04,Default,for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.64,0:13:49.72,Default,You just take those\Ndot strings files,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.72,0:13:53.52,Default,drag them into your application,\Ninto your Xcode project,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.90,0:13:56.32,Default,and then inspect them\Nwith a file inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.56,0:13:58.19,Default,And when you do, you're\Ngoing to see this button,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.30,0:14:00.41,Default,the top button there\Nthat says localize.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.68,0:14:02.78,Default,And when you click that,\Nthen you'll get a list
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.78,0:14:04.26,Default,of the languages, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.54,0:14:07.25,Default,And you can click however\Nmany of the languages you want
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.25,0:14:10.04,Default,to support localizing\Nthis string file for.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.23,0:14:13.88,Default,And then in your file navigator\Nyou'll see a dot strings file
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.88,0:14:14.51,Default,for every language.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.51,0:14:15.20,Default,You can click on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.35,0:14:17.98,Default,And then you -- usually what\Nyou'll do is you'll click on it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.98,0:14:19.58,Default,and you'll see hello\Nequal hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.77,0:14:22.48,Default,You'll take that entire file\Nor all the strings files,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.79,0:14:26.52,Default,ship them off to a localizer --\Nmaybe with a demo of your app
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.64,0:14:27.55,Default,or something like that --
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.82,0:14:29.84,Default,they'll translate all the\Nstrings and send them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.03,0:14:34.09,Default,And then you just plop them into\Nyour Xcode project and ship it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.14,0:14:41.41,Default,Okay. So the way that these\Nbundles are arranged is inside a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.41,0:14:44.04,Default,bundle -- and your\Napplication is the main bundle,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.04,0:14:45.61,Default,so that's the top level\Nof your application --
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.84,0:14:48.55,Default,inside are these\Nlproj directories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.99,0:14:50.97,Default,And the name of the\Nlproj directory is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:54.23,Default,like a little two-letter\Nsymbol for the language.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.23,0:14:56.53,Default,So there's EN dot\Nlproj; that's English.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.82,0:14:59.86,Default,There's FR dot lproj;\Nthat's French.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.15,0:15:03.13,Default,And inside the lproj is\Nall the strings files
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.77,0:15:05.38,Default,for localizing to that language.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.93,0:15:07.98,Default,Okay? It's as simple as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.05,0:15:11.32,Default,So you might have, you\Nknow, 25 dot lprojs
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.32,0:15:13.08,Default,if you support 25 languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.08,0:15:15.07,Default,In all them there will be a copy
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.07,0:15:18.49,Default,of the strings files\Nthat are edited.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.67,0:15:20.72,Default,You can look more about\NNS bundle offline,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.72,0:15:23.70,Default,but there are ways to also\Nassociate strings files not just
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.70,0:15:26.08,Default,with your main bundle of your\Napp, but if you had a framework
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.08,0:15:28.04,Default,or something else, you could\Nassociate it with frameworks
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.04,0:15:30.52,Default,because bundle, in\Naddition to main bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.52,0:15:32.16,Default,it has this bundle\Nfor class method.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.63,0:15:34.53,Default,Okay? And so it knows\Nwhere that class came from,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.53,0:15:36.52,Default,whether it was a framework\Nor your main bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.80,0:15:39.12,Default,And it will give you the bundle,\Nand then you can get a path
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.12,0:15:43.48,Default,for a resource or do localized\Nstring for key value table.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.16,0:15:47.81,Default,Okay. Couple of things about\Ndebugging localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.81,0:15:50.31,Default,There's a really nice user\Ndefault that you can set,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.31,0:15:52.56,Default,NS show non-localized strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.82,0:15:56.23,Default,And every time one of those\NNS localized string --
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.51,0:15:58.23,Default,I say methods, but\Nreally they're macros --
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.58,0:16:02.02,Default,any time one of those does not\Nfind an entry in a string file,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.06,0:16:03.01,Default,you'll get a little log.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.74,0:16:06.24,Default,Okay? So then you'll know that\Nyour localizer missed one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.18,0:16:09.28,Default,Okay. So that's important\Nto know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:12.38,Default,So that way when you're doing\Nyour QA of your localizations
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.38,0:16:14.70,Default,to make sure that they're\Nreally working as good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.02,0:16:16.97,Default,I've seen some people complain
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.97,0:16:20.05,Default,that sometimes they'll add\Nsome strings to a localization
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.23,0:16:21.71,Default,and test it and it's like, "Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.71,0:16:23.42,Default,it's not getting\Nthe new changes."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.81,0:16:28.04,Default,I haven't seen that in iOS 7,\Nbut if you do, building clean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.04,0:16:30.16,Default,and reinstalling seems\Nto solve that problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.16,0:16:32.61,Default,I don't know exactly\Nthe circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.61,0:16:33.83,Default,that supposedly happens under,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.83,0:16:35.19,Default,but it can't hurt\Nto build clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.41,0:16:38.62,Default,Okay. So that's strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.62,0:16:40.89,Default,And we'll see all this\Nhappening in the demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.50,0:16:44.27,Default,There's more to localization,\Nthough,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.27,0:16:45.80,Default,than just strings unfortunately.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.91,0:16:47.95,Default,There's also the\Nconcept of a locale.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.30,0:16:50.95,Default,So your user not only might\Nspeak a different language,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:54.95,Default,they might live in any\Nnumber of different locales.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.39,0:16:57.66,Default,An easy one to think\Nabout is English.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.90,0:16:59.75,Default,In America we speak English.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.75,0:17:01.82,Default,In Great Britain\Nthey speak English.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.08,0:17:05.25,Default,But there are local\Nidioms and the way
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.25,0:17:07.17,Default,that we express currency,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.42,0:17:10.30,Default,the way we even just express\Nnumbers -- big numbers --
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.30,0:17:12.85,Default,the commas and the periods\Nare swapped, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.09,0:17:14.47,Default,Things just are all\Nslightly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.47,0:17:15.88,Default,So even though language in both
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.88,0:17:17.95,Default,of those countries\Nwould be English,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.95,0:17:19.23,Default,the locales would be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.23,0:17:21.33,Default,So there's a whole other\Nsystem here for locales.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.65,0:17:23.11,Default,And users set their language
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.11,0:17:24.81,Default,and their locale using\Nthe settings app.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.30,0:17:27.70,Default,And your application it's\Njust supposed to adapt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.88,0:17:31.07,Default,Okay? And you adapt by\Nusing some of these methods
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.07,0:17:33.18,Default,that take a locale\Nas an argument
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.18,0:17:34.99,Default,or that use a locale\Nunder the covers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.99,0:17:37.47,Default,Okay? You can find out\Nwhat current locale is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.47,0:17:40.66,Default,with these methods, and you can\Nalso have this nice autoupdating
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:43.31,Default,current locale, which if the\Nuser changes their locale,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.31,0:17:45.44,Default,it will just automatically\Nupdate underneath the covers;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.84,0:17:49.08,Default,although, you probably want to\Nlisten to this radio station,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.08,0:17:51.89,Default,too, because if it changes, you\Nmight have to redraw your UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.28,0:17:53.31,Default,Right? If they change?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.31,0:17:56.08,Default,But it's pretty unusual for\Nthe user to change their locale
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.08,0:17:57.54,Default,or their language while\Nthey're in the middle
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.54,0:17:58.98,Default,of running your app,\Nbut it could happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.21,0:18:02.06,Default,Okay. You should be\Nprepared for that to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.46,0:18:04.73,Default,So what are some of the things\Nthat are different in a locale?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.73,0:18:06.26,Default,Well, there's numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.45,0:18:08.89,Default,Now, there's a lot going\Non with formatting numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.89,0:18:10.19,Default,It seems like it's\Nreally simple,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.26,0:18:12.00,Default,but there's actually a\Nlot to think about here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.26,0:18:14.68,Default,But I'm going to look at\Ntwo pretty simple cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.87,0:18:17.99,Default,One is displaying numbers\Nand one is reading numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.26,0:18:22.71,Default,So for displaying number on\Nscreen you're probably want
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.71,0:18:25.05,Default,to do string with\Nformat percent G.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.22,0:18:28.23,Default,"Percent G" just means\Ngeneric floating point number.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:30.38,Default,But you don't want\Nto do that, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.62,0:18:31.92,Default,What you want to do\Nis use this method
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.92,0:18:35.08,Default,in NS number formatter\Ncalled localized string
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.08,0:18:36.61,Default,from number, number style.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.89,0:18:38.15,Default,Okay. And there's\Ndifferent number styles
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.15,0:18:40.22,Default,like decimal and spell out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:41.20,Default,We'll even spell it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:42.31,Default,Like, if you put\Na four in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.31,0:18:43.78,Default,it will say four, f-o-u-r.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.90,0:18:45.04,Default,Okay, spell it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.04,0:18:46.94,Default,So there's different\Nformats for doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:49.30,Default,And that will give you back\Na string that you can put
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.30,0:18:51.31,Default,in the UI that will\Ndisplay the number
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.31,0:18:53.77,Default,in a way that's appropriate\Nfor the locale you're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.11,0:18:56.80,Default,And especially, again, a\Nlarge number like a thousand
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.09,0:19:00.95,Default,in the US might be one comma\Nzero zero zero point zero zero;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:03.64,Default,whereas in Great Britain it\Nwould be one period zero zero
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.64,0:19:04.92,Default,zero comma zero zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.42,0:19:07.04,Default,Okay. And so this\Nwould get that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.63,0:19:09.81,Default,Then there's parsing\Nnumbers, reading them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.13,0:19:14.80,Default,You really probably want\Nhere to just say int value
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.80,0:19:17.99,Default,or float value of a\Nstring, which will parse it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.99,0:19:21.22,Default,and try it interpret a float\Nor an int as the input.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.58,0:19:23.10,Default,But that's not really\Nthe right way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.10,0:19:24.85,Default,You should use the\Nnumber formatter here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.85,0:19:27.60,Default,So you just create a formatter,\Nset the style of number
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.60,0:19:28.63,Default,that you're trying to read in --
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.63,0:19:30.11,Default,same thing as we\Nsaw above there --
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.38,0:19:32.95,Default,and then you're going to get\Nthe parse number as in NS number
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.95,0:19:34.43,Default,by calling number from string.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.18,0:19:37.00,Default,Okay? And that's going\Nto look in that string,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.24,0:19:41.46,Default,parse it like a currency\Nor just a decimal number.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.69,0:19:42.83,Default,And so if the person types
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.83,0:19:45.52,Default,in one period zero zero\Nzero comma zero zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.52,0:19:48.00,Default,you'll get a thousand if they're\Nin the Great Britain locale.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.92,0:19:49.40,Default,Make sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:51.53,Default,Whereas in the US you\Nwouldn't get that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.53,0:19:54.31,Default,One period zero zero zero\Nprobably will give you one
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.47,0:19:55.58,Default,or might even give you nil
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.58,0:20:00.98,Default,because that's not\Nreally even a number.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.05,0:20:03.74,Default,Dates -- another complicated\None you have to be careful of.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.36,0:20:08.65,Default,All I'm going to say about\Ndates is familiarize yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.65,0:20:10.28,Default,with the concept\Nthat our calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.28,0:20:13.05,Default,the Gregorian calendar, is not\Nthe only calendar in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.53,0:20:15.38,Default,Okay? There are other\Ncalendars out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.68,0:20:19.63,Default,And there's mechanism in iOS\Nfor dealing with all of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.63,0:20:20.84,Default,but you have to know\Nhow to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.84,0:20:22.76,Default,I can't cover it all\Nin one lecture --
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.76,0:20:25.97,Default,even if I had a whole lecture\Ndevoted to it probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.21,0:20:28.98,Default,But you want to look at\Nclasses like NS calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.19,0:20:30.36,Default,search through the\Ndocumentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.36,0:20:31.45,Default,Kind of familiarize yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.45,0:20:34.74,Default,If you're really going\Nto do a multi-language,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.74,0:20:37.52,Default,multi-locale application, and\Ndates are part of your UI,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.52,0:20:40.44,Default,you really want to understand\Nwhat you're doing there, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.44,0:20:44.08,Default,For formatting simple dates\Nthere's this nice method,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.27,0:20:46.98,Default,localize string from\Ndate with the date style.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.39,0:20:52.60,Default,You can get away with a lot\Nby just using this one, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.77,0:20:55.46,Default,But if you're doing anything\Nmore complicated with dates
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.46,0:20:57.41,Default,like you're writing the\Ncalendar app or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.41,0:20:59.68,Default,then you obviously want to\Nreally understand dates better.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.10,0:21:04.49,Default,Strings, an interesting thing:\NIf you're searching in a string,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.81,0:21:07.44,Default,okay, especially if you're\Nsearching case insensitively
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.44,0:21:10.26,Default,to try and find a word in\Na string, you don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.26,0:21:11.86,Default,to use the range\Nof string method;
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.96,0:21:13.81,Default,you want to use this\Nrange of string method --
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.81,0:21:16.15,Default,range of string options\Nrange locale --
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.49,0:21:17.95,Default,and pass the current locale.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.37,0:21:20.96,Default,And this is especially true\Nwith case insensitivity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.96,0:21:22.64,Default,and when diacritics are involved
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.64,0:21:25.41,Default,because different\Nlanguages treat the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.41,0:21:26.57,Default,diacritics differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.78,0:21:29.04,Default,Okay? And case sensitivity\Nis different
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.04,0:21:30.01,Default,in different languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.35,0:21:33.31,Default,So you would definitely want\Nto use this method for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.31,0:21:35.11,Default,UI image is kind of\Nan interesting one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.11,0:21:38.63,Default,What if you were writing an\Napp, some kind of driving app
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.63,0:21:41.17,Default,or something like that\Nand you have a stop sign?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.43,0:21:44.73,Default,The stop sign is pretty much\Nthe same in almost all locales.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.77,0:21:45.48,Default,So you're good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.77,0:21:48.58,Default,But other signs, like yield\Nsigns and things like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.58,0:21:51.24,Default,can be quite different and your\Nuser wouldn't even recognize a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.24,0:21:52.92,Default,yield sign in their locale.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.27,0:21:54.82,Default,You might want to\Nhave a different image
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.82,0:21:57.31,Default,and have the image\Nbe localizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.89,0:21:59.78,Default,Okay? Really easy to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.78,0:22:03.27,Default,You just put the image\Nfor each locale, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.27,0:22:08.18,Default,in its lproj -- sorry -- for\Nthe languages in its lproj
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.57,0:22:10.11,Default,and then you pull it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.19,0:22:12.24,Default,But even there, if\Nyou have a language
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.24,0:22:14.01,Default,that might have different\Nlocales
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.01,0:22:17.32,Default,that have a different sign\Nwith the same language on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.54,0:22:21.20,Default,amazingly stop is\N"stop" in most languages,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.20,0:22:23.58,Default,even though "stop" is\Nobviously not a word in French.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.58,0:22:25.97,Default,If you go to France, you'll\Nsee stop signs that say "stop,"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.97,0:22:26.92,Default,which is kind of strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.30,0:22:29.75,Default,But there might be locales\Nwhere things are different,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.90,0:22:31.88,Default,so you might have to do a\Nlittle extra work on top
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.88,0:22:33.83,Default,of UI image image named.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.83,0:22:36.14,Default,Okay? You might have to say,\N"Oh, if I'm in this locale,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.14,0:22:37.10,Default,then it looks like this."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.10,0:22:40.06,Default,Now, again, that's only if\Nyou're doing an application
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.06,0:22:42.53,Default,that has imagery like road signs
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.53,0:22:44.54,Default,or whatever that's\Nvery locale-specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.77,0:22:47.29,Default,Okay? That's something a\Nlocalizer will hopefully
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.29,0:22:47.73,Default,help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.73,0:22:48.56,Default,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.56,0:22:50.28,Default,You'll put a yield sign\Nup, and they'll say, "Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.28,0:22:52.57,Default,wait a second in" -- you\Nknow, I don't know --
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.88,0:22:54.77,Default,"Sweden that looks different."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.77,0:22:57.14,Default,Or, you know, "In\NAfghanistan it's this."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.14,0:23:00.40,Default,And so your localizers\Nwill hopefully help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.40,0:23:04.29,Default,But UI image, image named will\Nlook in the lprojs for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.81,0:23:07.60,Default,Okay? You might still have\Nto locale on top of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.02,0:23:09.00,Default,So the demo we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.00,0:23:12.27,Default,to do here is internationalizing\NPhotoMania.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.27,0:23:17.32,Default,So I'm going to start with\Nthe PhotoMania that we had
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.88,0:23:20.92,Default,at our last lecture, last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.92,0:23:21.96,Default,So here's PhotoMania.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.59,0:23:26.20,Default,And PhotoMania is UI here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.56,0:23:29.09,Default,It's amazing, it's actually\Npretty easy to localize
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.13,0:23:33.71,Default,because PhotoMania, primarily\Nwhat it displays is its content.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.03,0:23:37.30,Default,Right? If you look at\Nalmost all of this UI,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.04,0:23:41.47,Default,it's just only displaying\Nwhat's coming back from Flickr.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.47,0:23:43.68,Default,It hardly has any\Nother text in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.87,0:23:46.02,Default,That's actually very\Ngood UI design.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.22,0:23:48.69,Default,Generally, you want as\Nhigh a percentage of the UI
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.97,0:23:52.21,Default,to be what you're displaying --\Nso if you're photo viewing app,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.21,0:23:54.98,Default,you would want photo\Neverywhere and just a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.98,0:23:57.04,Default,of controls around the edges.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.39,0:23:59.10,Default,But there is a couple of places.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.10,0:24:02.43,Default,You can see this guy right\Nhere has quite a few strings
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.43,0:24:03.22,Default,in it right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.49,0:24:06.68,Default,And there's some miscellaneous\Nstrings that we load up as part
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.68,0:24:10.99,Default,of these prototype cells that\Nmight need to be localizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.35,0:24:16.30,Default,But let's start, like I\Nsaid, with adding the ability
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.30,0:24:17.71,Default,to have these other languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.94,0:24:24.66,Default,And we do that by clicking\Nhere to edit our project.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.00,0:24:25.91,Default,But again, we don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.91,0:24:28.46,Default,to be editing the target;\Nwe want to edit this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.46,0:24:29.84,Default,So this is something right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.97,0:24:31.28,Default,Don't forget this\Nstep right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.28,0:24:32.59,Default,We want the project.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.59,0:24:35.40,Default,And when we do that, now you'll\Nsee there's localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.40,0:24:36.97,Default,Here's the localizations\Ndown here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.29,0:24:39.92,Default,And we are going to\Nuse base localization,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.04,0:24:43.24,Default,which means our storyboard\Nis going to be our base
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.24,0:24:45.09,Default,and we're going to modify\Nthe strings after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.09,0:24:46.57,Default,So I'm going to add French.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.62,0:24:48.57,Default,So let's add French.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.81,0:24:52.50,Default,It's asking me, "What\Nexisting stuff do you want
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.50,0:24:54.03,Default,to make strings files for?"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.03,0:24:56.67,Default,And I'm just going to say\Nall of it, all my storyboards
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.67,0:24:59.26,Default,and don't worry too much\Nabout info P list dot strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.26,0:25:00.79,Default,There's a little bit\Nin there to localize,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.79,0:25:02.77,Default,like your app name can\Nactually be localized.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.77,0:25:05.49,Default,But most of your stuff\Nis in your storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.49,0:25:06.99,Default,So we'll have both storyboards.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.46,0:25:09.88,Default,And when we do that, it\Njust adds French here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.40,0:25:12.59,Default,And if we look up\Nhere, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.59,0:25:15.80,Default,Now this has a little\Ntriangle that, if we click it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.32,0:25:18.97,Default,we get to see that\Nthere's the base storyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.56,0:25:22.19,Default,and now there's string\Nfiles for French.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.64,0:25:24.75,Default,Okay? So here's what a\Nstrings file looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.15,0:25:26.89,Default,It's got a comment\Nto the localizer,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.19,0:25:29.65,Default,and then a key, and\Nthen a value.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.09,0:25:32.64,Default,Okay? Now, these\Nkeys right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.81,0:25:35.39,Default,how do we know what\Nmatches up with what?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.39,0:25:37.97,Default,Well, most of the time we can\Nlook at the value like done.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.27,0:25:41.02,Default,Well, we know that done is\Nthis done button -- easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.37,0:25:42.54,Default,But look at title.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.19,0:25:45.94,Default,See, there's two, three titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.94,0:25:48.73,Default,There's a title right here and\Nthere's two title right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.73,0:25:51.00,Default,It's like which title is which?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.42,0:25:52.40,Default,Which is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.71,0:25:56.70,Default,And which is this title\Nright here, for example?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.29,0:26:00.14,Default,And you can find that out by\Nclicking on any of the titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.14,0:26:01.15,Default,Like, let's click on this one
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.15,0:26:03.07,Default,because we do definitely\Nwant to localize this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.48,0:26:06.99,Default,Go over to the inspector, go\Nto the identity inspector --
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.99,0:26:08.16,Default,it's part of its identity --
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.39,0:26:10.94,Default,and you can see that all\Nobjects have an object ID
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.56,0:26:12.30,Default,in a storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.68,0:26:13.13,Default,You see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.65,0:26:16.23,Default,So this one's 65EYS hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.70,0:26:18.57,Default,So that is this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.77,0:26:22.43,Default,Okay? So this one is the title\Nthat is the title of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.89,0:26:26.91,Default,Now, these other two titles, we\Ndon't even need to localize them
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.42,0:26:32.79,Default,because they are in these\Nprototypes here, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.10,0:26:35.77,Default,These two prototypes, so they\Nnever appear on the UI, right,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.94,0:26:36.91,Default,these titles and subtitles.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.91,0:26:38.12,Default,We always drive them
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.49,0:26:42.22,Default,with whatever our data\Nsource is for our table view.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.22,0:26:44.08,Default,But this one we do\Nneed to localize,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.08,0:26:46.09,Default,and then also this\Nlittle subtitle one here,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.09,0:26:46.86,Default,too, which is QCJ.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.02,0:26:49.56,Default,This one also needs\Nto be localized.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.94,0:26:51.71,Default,So what does it look\Nlike to localize these?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.71,0:26:53.75,Default,Let's say I'm a localizer\Nand I'm localizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.94,0:26:55.95,Default,Unfortunately, I don't\Nquite know enough French
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.95,0:26:57.05,Default,to localize this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.05,0:27:00.43,Default,So I'm going to show you a\Nkind of cool way to localize --
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.76,0:27:03.50,Default,which is good for testing --\Nwhich is just to put a period
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.91,0:27:05.73,Default,between every letter like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.40,0:27:09.83,Default,Okay. So do a localization\Nlike this as a developer
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.83,0:27:11.30,Default,because it's easy for you to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.30,0:27:12.79,Default,Okay? You don't have\Nto know the language.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.97,0:27:15.53,Default,And what's cool about this\Nis it makes everything wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.84,0:27:17.86,Default,So it's going to\Nreally challenge your UI
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.46,0:27:20.89,Default,to make things fit when you\Nchange these strings, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.89,0:27:24.10,Default,It might even work for German if\Nyou do this because German tends
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.10,0:27:25.68,Default,to be very long words.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.19,0:27:29.22,Default,And it's also, again, really --\Nyou can do it really quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.22,0:27:33.59,Default,Let's go ahead and localize\Nthis entire file by doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.50,0:27:39.58,Default,Oops. And another good thing\Nabout this is everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.58,0:27:41.06,Default,in the UI that this appears,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.12,0:27:43.67,Default,it's going to be really\Nobvious immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.80,0:27:45.64,Default,Oops. I forgot that one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.64,0:27:50.67,Default,Because this period's very,\Nvery easy to see in the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.16,0:27:53.43,Default,So we don't need to do these\Ntwo titles or this subtitle.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.43,0:27:56.60,Default,We don't need to do this because\Nthat's just a placeholder.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.17,0:27:59.20,Default,We want this subtitle\Ndown here, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.20,0:28:01.86,Default,because that's the\Nother subtitle.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.20,0:28:03.68,Default,We want this one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.30,0:28:08.41,Default,And so the little URL guy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.42,0:28:10.10,Default,And cancel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.07,0:28:14.84,Default,Okay? So we've localized\Nthis entire thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.17,0:28:18.06,Default,everything that needs to\Nbe localized to French.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.18,0:28:19.82,Default,And you might even --\Nwhen you send this off
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.82,0:28:22.19,Default,to the localizer you might even\Ntake these things out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.57,0:28:24.82,Default,So the localizer\Non this one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.18,0:28:27.63,Default,The localizer doesn't even\Nget confused, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.63,0:28:28.26,Default,like, what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.52,0:28:30.24,Default,However, there's some\Narguments to leave them
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.24,0:28:31.68,Default,in because you're going to put
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.68,0:28:34.73,Default,that little NS show\Nnon-localized strings --
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.92,0:28:36.29,Default,the user default\NI talked about --
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.29,0:28:38.71,Default,on, and then you're going to\Ncomplaint about all these ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.92,0:28:41.29,Default,So its kinda, 6 in one hand,\Nhalf dozen in the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.32,0:28:42.09,Default,if you want to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.91,0:28:43.23,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.23,0:28:44.51,Default,So now we've localized this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.51,0:28:45.29,Default,What does it look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.29,0:28:48.03,Default,So let's run this and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.18,0:28:49.43,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.70,0:28:52.84,Default,So when we run this\NUI, it all looks
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.84,0:28:54.23,Default,like it's in English, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.46,0:28:59.04,Default,And in fact, if we go over to\Nour little add photo guy right
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.04,0:29:00.75,Default,here, this all looks\Nto be English
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.75,0:29:01.69,Default,and everything looks fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.15,0:29:03.37,Default,Okay? Nothing has changed
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.37,0:29:04.68,Default,because we're not\Nrunning in French.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.79,0:29:05.69,Default,We're still running in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.69,0:29:08.02,Default,So the base storyboard\Nis still showing through.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.24,0:29:08.87,Default,Okay, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.87,0:29:09.77,Default,That's a good thing to check,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.90,0:29:12.54,Default,to make sure you\Nhaven't broken anything
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.63,0:29:14.03,Default,by adding a localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.37,0:29:18.23,Default,But now let's go and change\Nthe language to be French.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.23,0:29:20.58,Default,So you do that, you can\Ndo it in the simulator
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.63,0:29:21.83,Default,and you can do it\Non your device.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.22,0:29:26.55,Default,And you just go here to general,\Ninternational, language --
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.55,0:29:27.68,Default,we'll change it to French.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.53,0:29:30.27,Default,Okay. It's changing\Nthe language.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.76,0:29:33.03,Default,Your application, if it\Nwas running right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.03,0:29:35.93,Default,would get that notification\Nthat we talked about that says,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.93,0:29:37.73,Default,"Oh, this has changed."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.73,0:29:39.50,Default,So you could redraw your UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.97,0:29:46.70,Default,But let's go back and run\Nhere and see what we get.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.79,0:29:48.04,Default,So here's photographer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.31,0:29:51.23,Default,Hopefully this is going to\Nfill in with its normal data.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.69,0:29:52.43,Default,Yes, it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.81,0:29:55.84,Default,Let's go over here\Nand look here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.84,0:30:01.31,Default,And you can see that it has done\Nour little dot language here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.31,0:30:02.33,Default,We switched it to French
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.42,0:30:03.80,Default,and it's done our\Nlittle dot language,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.06,0:30:05.44,Default,but we can't really\Nread everything
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.49,0:30:06.79,Default,because nothing fits, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.79,0:30:08.22,Default,Subtitle doesn't fit, title.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.22,0:30:10.37,Default,So this is good that it\Ndoesn't fit, and this is part
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.37,0:30:12.05,Default,of the advantage\Nof doing the dots.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.05,0:30:13.44,Default,Also notice this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.81,0:30:15.17,Default,This is all still in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.52,0:30:17.68,Default,So that's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.02,0:30:19.32,Default,So let's fix these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.32,0:30:21.86,Default,The things not fitting\Nis quite easy to fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.94,0:30:23.91,Default,We're just going to go to\Nthe storyboard right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.20,0:30:29.26,Default,and I'm going to reset\Nto use Auto Layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.96,0:30:32.52,Default,Okay. Now when I dragged\Nall these things in,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.52,0:30:34.61,Default,I believe I used the blue lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.87,0:30:38.50,Default,So when I reset to suggested\Nconstraints, I think I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.50,0:30:40.91,Default,to get suggested\Nconstraints that work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.91,0:30:43.86,Default,So let's go ahead\Nand take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.86,0:30:46.07,Default,Enter enough and you can see\Nnow all these things fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.16,0:30:50.40,Default,See that? Cancel\Nfits, done, title.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.24,0:30:54.15,Default,Okay? So we did a good\Njob with our Auto Layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.15,0:30:57.18,Default,So Auto Layout is a fundamental\Npart of localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.40,0:30:58.35,Default,Fundamental.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.90,0:31:00.98,Default,Okay? If you don't have\Nyour Auto Layout right,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.18,0:31:02.56,Default,you cannot do localization
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.76,0:31:03.97,Default,because when you\Nchange the strings,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.97,0:31:06.15,Default,everything will be cut\Noff, and dot dot dot,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.15,0:31:07.15,Default,and all this bad stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.34,0:31:09.25,Default,But what about this\NEnglish right here?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.25,0:31:10.95,Default,We got to fix this, we\Ngot to get rid of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.42,0:31:13.93,Default,And these are actually\Nnot in my storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.93,0:31:16.43,Default,These strings, like "Okay,"\Nand "Add photo," and "Sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.43,0:31:17.77,Default,this device cannot add a photo,"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.14,0:31:20.53,Default,those are all literal\Nstrings in my code.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.02,0:31:22.65,Default,So let's go localize those.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.43,0:31:26.41,Default,And those are all in the\Nthing we added last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.41,0:31:28.28,Default,So hopefully you remember\Nsome of this code,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.56,0:31:30.38,Default,which is add photo\Nview controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.25,0:31:33.37,Default,Okay? So here's add\Nphoto view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.37,0:31:35.96,Default,So one thing I like\Nto do in anything
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.96,0:31:39.36,Default,that I implement is\Nsearch for at sign quote.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.09,0:31:42.98,Default,Okay? Because at sign quote is\Ngoing to be literal strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.98,0:31:45.65,Default,Now, not all literal\Nstrings need to be localized.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.73,0:31:48.53,Default,Okay? But like, this\None does, and this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.61,0:31:49.86,Default,and this one, and this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.54,0:31:53.46,Default,This one not; this is\Na segue identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.69,0:31:54.57,Default,Never appears in the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.84,0:31:56.23,Default,Does not need to be localized.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.48,0:32:00.18,Default,This one also not; this\Nis the name of an entity
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.18,0:32:02.37,Default,in the database -- or at least\Nin this case we don't put this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.37,0:32:04.48,Default,in the UI, although we do\Nsomewhere else in the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.48,0:32:06.38,Default,A little preview of what\Nwe're going to do later.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.82,0:32:09.11,Default,And then, of course,\Nall of these need
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.11,0:32:10.67,Default,to be localized, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.86,0:32:11.84,Default,This one also.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.93,0:32:13.41,Default,All these things do is alerts.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.80,0:32:15.56,Default,This one not; this is thumbnail.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.56,0:32:17.07,Default,This is just a little\Nfile extension
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.07,0:32:19.61,Default,for our thumbnail URL --\Nnever appears in the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.13,0:32:21.77,Default,Here's another one that\Nnever appears the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.77,0:32:24.57,Default,This is how we're making\Na unique document URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.26,0:32:27.60,Default,So here we don't need to\Nuse a number formatter
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.60,0:32:28.45,Default,and all that business.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.86,0:32:31.56,Default,And then here's some\Nmore of the filter stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.80,0:32:33.74,Default,Notice in the filter\Nstuff this does not need
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.74,0:32:35.37,Default,to be localized, but this does.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.85,0:32:38.09,Default,This appears in the action\Nsheet; this is just used
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.09,0:32:39.42,Default,in the code behind the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.86,0:32:42.99,Default,So we only have to do these\Nchrome, blur, noir, and fade.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.79,0:32:46.91,Default,Okay? So that's the stuff\Nthat needs to be localized.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.91,0:32:47.98,Default,So how are we going\Nto localize that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.98,0:32:49.31,Default,Let's pick one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.31,0:32:53.28,Default,How about let's pick this\None right here: "Sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.28,0:32:54.41,Default,this device cannot add a photo."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.41,0:32:56.32,Default,Because we know that's\Ngoing to come up right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.60,0:32:58.49,Default,So how would we localize this?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.11,0:33:03.43,Default,Some of this is art of\Nprogramming; some of it is kind
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.43,0:33:06.13,Default,of what's a way that's really\Ngoing to work effectively?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.42,0:33:10.34,Default,But I think one of the best\Nways to do this is to get rid
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.34,0:33:12.73,Default,of this literal string\Nand replace it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.73,0:33:14.73,Default,with something you\Npound sign define.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.73,0:33:21.96,Default,So I'm going to call this\None "Alert can't add photo."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.96,0:33:26.61,Default,Okay? And I'm actually going\Nto put a little comment here
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.61,0:33:27.67,Default,and paste that thing back
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.67,0:33:30.02,Default,so I can remember what\NI originally intended
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.02,0:33:30.94,Default,to say in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.44,0:33:33.69,Default,And then I'm going to\Nadd a pound sign define
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.69,0:33:37.58,Default,for this alert, can't add photo\Nthat's an NS localized string --
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.52,0:33:40.07,Default,that macro NS localized string.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.07,0:33:41.47,Default,In fact, NS localized\Nstring from table.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.47,0:33:45.13,Default,So I'm going to put those up\Nhere in my alert section here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.53,0:33:51.21,Default,So I'm just going to pound\Nsign define can't add photo
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.21,0:33:54.80,Default,to be NS localized\Nstring from table.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.23,0:33:56.82,Default,So I have to give it the string.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.87,0:34:01.19,Default,And here, one thing you could\Nsay here is you could put the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.19,0:34:02.26,Default,English version here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.49,0:34:05.25,Default,And a nice thing about putting\Nthe English version here is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.25,0:34:08.59,Default,that if you don't localize it,\Nyou'll get English at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.07,0:34:12.10,Default,But I actually don't\Nbelieve in that strategy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.39,0:34:16.49,Default,because if I'm French and I\Nget English, it looks bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.49,0:34:18.13,Default,It makes my app look bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.17,0:34:19.95,Default,It's almost better\Nto get some kind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.99,0:34:22.64,Default,of internal thing that's like,\N"Oh, this app is broken."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.64,0:34:24.74,Default,It will be found in\Ntesting right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.94,0:34:29.44,Default,There's many places that\Nyou would ship your app
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.65,0:34:32.77,Default,to get offended if you\Nthrow English in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.98,0:34:34.69,Default,They're kind of like,\N"Oh yeah, English.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.69,0:34:35.62,Default,Great." You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.91,0:34:37.26,Default,So it's almost better\Nnot to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.43,0:34:39.93,Default,Also, there's another problem\Nhere, which is that what
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.93,0:34:43.50,Default,if this word is a simple\Nword like "alert" or "yes"?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.80,0:34:48.38,Default,Okay? Well, there can only be\Nthis key into this table once.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.49,0:34:51.22,Default,And so if that yes might want\Nto be two different words
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.22,0:34:53.62,Default,in a different language, there's\Nno way to distinguish them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.23,0:34:56.52,Default,Okay? You would just\Nyes would be the key,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.52,0:34:59.79,Default,and you can only convert\Nyes to "oui" or whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.79,0:35:01.49,Default,but you can't do anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.73,0:35:05.02,Default,So what I do is I\Nactually put this --
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.63,0:35:07.45,Default,this internal define\N-- into here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.45,0:35:08.32,Default,So that's the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.58,0:35:12.22,Default,What that means is I have to\Nprovide an English dot strings
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.93,0:35:15.39,Default,because otherwise this is\Ngoing to appear in the UI
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.39,0:35:16.93,Default,because that's the default.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.34,0:35:20.98,Default,Okay? So I'm going\Nto have to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.05,0:35:25.11,Default,I also am going to give the\Ncomment for the localizer here,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.11,0:35:30.51,Default,I'm just going to say, "This\Nis message given to user
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.51,0:35:36.55,Default,if the user tries to add a photo
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.82,0:35:41.46,Default,but there is an unrecoverable\Nproblem."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.76,0:35:43.62,Default,Okay. Because that's\Nwhen this is shown.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.62,0:35:45.49,Default,This can't add photo\Nhappens right here
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.89,0:35:47.92,Default,with when can't add\Nphoto returns no.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.92,0:35:51.85,Default,So this is something like, "I\Ncan't get where your location is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.85,0:35:53.91,Default,on Earth, but it's\Nbecause you're restricted.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.91,0:35:56.62,Default,So there's nothing you can do\Nabout it" or "There's no camera
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.62,0:35:58.60,Default,on this device, so there's\Nnothing you can do about it."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.06,0:36:00.91,Default,So -- oops, wrong button there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.94,0:36:04.40,Default,So it's an unrecoverable error.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.40,0:36:05.59,Default,So I'm trying to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.59,0:36:09.05,Default,to the localizer here what\Nthis message is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.27,0:36:11.27,Default,And I'm also going\Nto put it in a table.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.27,0:36:14.29,Default,I'm using localized string\Nfrom table, and I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.29,0:36:17.56,Default,to call the table the "add\Nphoto view controller table."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.25,0:36:21.32,Default,Okay? So that means that when\NI run that genstrings thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.52,0:36:23.89,Default,it's going to generate a strings\Nfile called add photo view
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.89,0:36:25.05,Default,controller dot strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.44,0:36:26.72,Default,And that's where it's\Ngoing to put this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.04,0:36:29.33,Default,So I'm kind of collecting\Nall the strings
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.53,0:36:31.57,Default,for this particular\Nview controller
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.57,0:36:32.62,Default,into one strings file.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.62,0:36:35.33,Default,I could separate it\Neven more fine grained,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.33,0:36:36.35,Default,or I could put all the strings
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.35,0:36:37.69,Default,in my whole app into\None big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.69,0:36:38.60,Default,That's possible, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.13,0:36:39.27,Default,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.07,0:36:44.49,Default,>> Would it be beneficial to\Npass the original string along
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.62,0:36:45.71,Default,to the localizer somehow?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.29,0:36:49.35,Default,>> Yeah. So the question\Nis: Would it be beneficial
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.35,0:36:51.79,Default,to let the localizer\Nsee the English string?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.99,0:36:52.71,Default,Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.71,0:36:55.40,Default,And when you send this\NFrench dot string --
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.40,0:36:57.53,Default,French version of the strings\N-- off to the French localizer,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.73,0:37:00.42,Default,you'll want to send the English\None, too, so they can see, "Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.42,0:37:01.58,Default,I see what this is in English."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.58,0:37:04.05,Default,And in fact, when we do our\Nlocalization we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.05,0:37:05.93,Default,to start with the English\None and we'll go to French.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.93,0:37:07.34,Default,So there's that one.
