Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.63,0:46:38.91,Default,And now when we run, we'll see
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.16,0:46:41.65,Default,that we get photographer\Nalong the top here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.35,0:46:44.37,Default,Okay? So that's an example\Nof where you need to localize
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.37,0:46:45.90,Default,by actually calling\Nthe bundle thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.90,0:46:47.45,Default,as opposed to NS\Nlocalized string.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.82,0:46:48.15,Default,Question?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.34,0:46:52.97,Default,>> When you did the macro
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.15,0:46:55.70,Default,for the NS localized\Nyou [inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.70,0:47:00.11,Default,If I have two dot M\Nwith the same string,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.16,0:47:01.46,Default,could I put that in\Nthe dot H [inaudible]?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.76,0:47:02.44,Default,>> Yeah. Great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.44,0:47:06.13,Default,So the question is: When I did\Nthese NS localized strings here
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.13,0:47:08.80,Default,I put them in my dot M --\Nphoto view controller dot M --
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.80,0:47:10.30,Default,see how I put them\Nall right in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.61,0:47:15.39,Default,Could I put these in a dot H\Nsomewhere and then import them
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.39,0:47:16.52,Default,and share them between two?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.74,0:47:18.31,Default,The answer is absolutely\Nyou can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.31,0:47:21.63,Default,When you do genstrings, it's\Nlegal to put a dot H file there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.63,0:47:24.62,Default,In fact, genstrings will look\Nin any file you want, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.73,0:47:26.47,Default,So yes, you can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.42,0:47:28.31,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.77,0:47:30.40,Default,So that's it for localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.83,0:47:32.32,Default,I'm just kind of skimming\Nthe surface as far
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.32,0:47:34.83,Default,as of localization, but I think\Nthis is a really important one
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.83,0:47:37.42,Default,to know if you're going to\Nship a product on the app store
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.73,0:47:39.55,Default,because you can really\Nopen up your market
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.86,0:47:41.61,Default,by having it localized.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.61,0:47:44.83,Default,It's not that expensive to have\Nthese strings files localized.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.14,0:47:49.37,Default,Really, more of your cost\Nis sometimes just QA-ing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.52,0:47:51.95,Default,You got to put something\Nthat's in French in front
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.95,0:47:55.14,Default,of French users and make sure\Nthat it uses the right idioms
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.14,0:47:56.33,Default,and that it's understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.33,0:47:59.40,Default,And, you know, if you get a good\Nlocalization company doing the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.40,0:48:01.82,Default,localization for you,\Nthey'll do the QA as well
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.82,0:48:02.96,Default,and make sure that, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.26,0:48:04.90,Default,it's actually user-tested\Nas well.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.69,0:48:07.60,Default,Okay? All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.39,0:48:09.70,Default,Back to the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.14,0:48:10.41,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.83,0:48:15.76,Default,Okay. The last thing\Nwe're going to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.76,0:48:19.08,Default,about here is settings, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.35,0:48:22.47,Default,So settings allows you\Nto add user interface
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.68,0:48:25.54,Default,for your application into\Nthe general settings app.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.54,0:48:28.00,Default,So you can see the screen\Ncapture at the bottom there,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.00,0:48:29.44,Default,that's the general settings app.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.85,0:48:32.83,Default,And if you scroll down towards\Nthe bottom of very first page
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.83,0:48:35.58,Default,of settings, you can see all\Nthese other apps, like Maps
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.58,0:48:37.25,Default,and Safari and even\Nthird-party apps --
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.25,0:48:38.91,Default,Twitter, Facebook,\NFlickr, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.91,0:48:40.41,Default,Actually, I'm not sure\Nthose are third-party apps;
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.41,0:48:44.21,Default,they're probably iOS 7's\Nintegration to those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.64,0:48:47.60,Default,But your apps could appear\Nat the bottom of this list.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.60,0:48:49.50,Default,And when you click\Non one of those apps,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.76,0:48:53.86,Default,it goes to the next view here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.86,0:48:54.94,Default,And I've shown two\Ndifferent ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.94,0:48:56.39,Default,one for Maps and one for Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.68,0:48:58.39,Default,And you can see that there\Nare some UI in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.59,0:49:03.92,Default,We got some switches, we can\Nchoose from a predefined list
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.92,0:49:05.81,Default,of things like where it\Nsays search engine Google.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.81,0:49:07.64,Default,You can click on that and\Nhave a list of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.64,0:49:10.40,Default,You can also have\Nsliders in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.54,0:49:13.98,Default,You can group things, etc.\NSo this UI you can build
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.98,0:49:16.36,Default,for your app and have\Nthe settings app do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.68,0:49:22.50,Default,This UI is basically a UI\Non top of NS user defaults.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.46,0:49:26.57,Default,Okay? So these things -- all\Nthese things in the UI --
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.76,0:49:28.56,Default,are setting NS user defaults.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.56,0:49:29.33,Default,That's all they're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.48,0:49:30.91,Default,And that's how it's\Ncommunicating
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.91,0:49:32.25,Default,with your app, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.68,0:49:33.76,Default,So it's as simple as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.03,0:49:36.23,Default,There's really not a lot\Nof UI you can put in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.56,0:49:38.46,Default,I'm not going to talk about\Nall the things you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.46,0:49:40.29,Default,You can look in the\Ndocumentation for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.57,0:49:44.07,Default,But like I said, sliders,\Nswitches, text fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.35,0:49:46.76,Default,typeable text fields,\Nand also selecting
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.76,0:49:48.05,Default,from lists are the main things.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.59,0:49:52.23,Default,The way you add this to your\Napp is in your app, okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.49,0:49:55.98,Default,you go into Xcode\Nand you say new file.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.13,0:49:59.02,Default,And then under resources\Nyou pick settings bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.08,0:50:00.08,Default,This is the same place we went
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.08,0:50:01.61,Default,to add a strings\Nfile a moment ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.95,0:50:03.23,Default,Now we're going to\Ndo settings bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.48,0:50:06.02,Default,And when you do settings\Nbundle you'll get this little
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.02,0:50:06.76,Default,settings bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.76,0:50:08.13,Default,Add it to your file\Nnavigation there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.36,0:50:09.89,Default,You can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.89,0:50:12.83,Default,And it's going to give\Nyou a default kind
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.83,0:50:15.30,Default,of an example bundle,\Nwhich is really nice
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.30,0:50:18.52,Default,because it's a good starting\Npoint to get started,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.52,0:50:19.93,Default,and what can I do\Nwith this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.51,0:50:22.99,Default,All that UI that you're going\Nto build, you don't build it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.99,0:50:25.21,Default,in a storyboard, you\Ndon't build it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.49,0:50:29.37,Default,with graphical interface; you\Nbuild it using a property list.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.66,0:50:32.78,Default,Okay? And this property list has\Nwell-defined keys and values.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.03,0:50:34.96,Default,And these keys and values\Ndetermine whether you're doing a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.96,0:50:38.51,Default,text field, or a slider, or\Ngrouping things, or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.51,0:50:41.24,Default,So you can kind of\Nsee up here some
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.31,0:50:45.05,Default,of the property list things\Nyou can set to build this UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.05,0:50:47.37,Default,For example, what\Nyou see on screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.37,0:50:48.74,Default,I'm going to show\Nyou what that looks
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.74,0:50:50.48,Default,like in the settings app, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.66,0:50:53.00,Default,So you see you got a\Ngroup is item zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.00,0:50:54.24,Default,So this thing is\Ngoing to be grouped.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.49,0:50:55.92,Default,The name of the group is\N"group," so it's going
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.92,0:50:57.01,Default,to say group at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.20,0:51:01.10,Default,And then we got a text field,\Na toggle switch, and a slider.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.10,0:51:02.78,Default,You see items one,\Ntwo, and three?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.16,0:51:09.57,Default,The text field there, you know,\Nusing the alphabetic keyboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.57,0:51:12.41,Default,it doesn't do auto correction,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.80,0:51:18.01,Default,etc. The toggle switch,\Nits title is enabled.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.01,0:51:19.79,Default,So it's going to say enabled,\Nand then there's going
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.79,0:51:21.67,Default,to be a toggle switch there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.96,0:51:24.92,Default,The slider looks like it\Ngoes from a zero to one.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.18,0:51:26.58,Default,And for all three of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.58,0:51:28.95,Default,do you see how it says\Nname underbar preference,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.02,0:51:31.75,Default,enabled underbar preference,\Nslider underbar preference
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.75,0:51:32.91,Default,in each of those three things?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.22,0:51:36.38,Default,That's the NS user default\Nthat it's setting, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.23,0:51:40.39,Default,I don't really like\Nthose names very much,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.39,0:51:41.45,Default,but that's what it's setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.45,0:51:42.93,Default,So what is this going\Nto look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.93,0:51:44.46,Default,What would this particular\Nthing look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.46,0:51:46.78,Default,Well, it would look\Nlike this, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.11,0:51:49.79,Default,Grouped, name, enabled with a\Nswitch, and then the slider.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.84,0:51:54.87,Default,Okay? So localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.87,0:51:56.32,Default,Let's talk about\Nlocalization settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.32,0:51:57.95,Default,You've got to have\Nlocalization for setting,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.19,0:51:59.71,Default,otherwise when a person's\NFrench they're not going
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.71,0:52:00.93,Default,to understand how\Nto do your settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.32,0:52:03.82,Default,And it's done using\Nstrings files.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.07,0:52:06.04,Default,And if you look inside\Nthe settings bundle,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.04,0:52:08.47,Default,you'll see it comes\Nwith an EN dot lproj;
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.52,0:52:10.53,Default,little bit of English\Nbias there, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.96,0:52:12.75,Default,And in that EN dot lproj --
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.82,0:52:15.14,Default,actually, might not\Neven be English bias.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.14,0:52:17.31,Default,It's possible that if\Nyou're developing this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.31,0:52:20.85,Default,and you're French, it might\Ncreate an FR dot lproj for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.97,0:52:22.02,Default,I'm not sure, I've\Nnever tried that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.49,0:52:25.95,Default,And then inside this\Nstring's file is every string
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.95,0:52:28.45,Default,that would appear in this\NUI that you're building
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.87,0:52:31.41,Default,with equals whatever\Nit's supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.14,0:52:37.18,Default,Okay? So whatever's in that base\NP list we saw two slides ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.45,0:52:38.24,Default,anything that would appear
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.24,0:52:40.37,Default,in the UI you can just say\Nit equals something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.71,0:52:43.08,Default,And then you can have as many\Ndot lprojs as you want here --
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.08,0:52:44.40,Default,French dot lproj, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.12,0:52:47.81,Default,The bad thing is\Nthere's no way to go
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.81,0:52:49.55,Default,to the file inspector\Nand hit localize.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.11,0:52:51.93,Default,Okay? For some reason\Nthey have not gotten
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.93,0:52:55.62,Default,around to having the settings\Nbundle be localizable in Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.18,0:52:57.49,Default,It's got the mechanism there,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.49,0:53:00.17,Default,but there's no inspector\NUI to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.49,0:53:02.78,Default,So how do you localize\Nthis thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.78,0:53:05.09,Default,How do I create an FR dot lproj?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.51,0:53:09.13,Default,And the answer is you're\Ngoing to go to finder
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.48,0:53:11.10,Default,and find this settings bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.10,0:53:12.54,Default,You can actually\Ndo that from Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.54,0:53:13.90,Default,I'll show you how to\Ndo that in the demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.15,0:53:16.25,Default,Then you're going to right-click\Non the settings bundle
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.25,0:53:18.18,Default,and say show package contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.38,0:53:19.91,Default,And that's going to\Nshow you what's inside
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.91,0:53:22.52,Default,that settings bundle, which\Nis going to look like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.79,0:53:24.90,Default,And you're going to see\Nthe EN dot lproj there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.19,0:53:28.87,Default,And now you're going to\Nmanually create an FR dot lproj.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.29,0:53:31.86,Default,Okay? Really nice\Nsupport for it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.30,0:53:34.75,Default,And usually I do this by\Ntaking the EN dot lproj
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.75,0:53:36.69,Default,and just copying and pasting\Nit and then renaming it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.87,0:53:40.52,Default,from EN dot lproj\Ncopy to FR dot lproj.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.85,0:53:43.43,Default,And then the root dot\Nstrings that's inside there,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.65,0:53:45.82,Default,that's what I would send\Noff to my localizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.71,0:53:49.47,Default,Okay? And that would do the\Nequals thing for French.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.12,0:53:52.61,Default,So let's see what this\Nlooks like in Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.31,0:53:57.26,Default,Okay? Because Bouncer has some\Nnice settings that we could set.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.47,0:53:59.96,Default,And what I'm going to do is\Nmake it so the elasticity --
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.96,0:54:02.60,Default,you know, the bounciness\Nof the bouncing ball --
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.84,0:54:04.44,Default,is settable in settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.59,0:54:06.94,Default,So right now we have the\Nelasticity set at one,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.24,0:54:10.69,Default,which is kind of the maximum\Nelasticity that it can have
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.69,0:54:11.95,Default,and still settle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.00,0:54:14.69,Default,If we had more than one, it\Nwould start getting faster
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.69,0:54:16.15,Default,and faster as it\Nbounced off the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.37,0:54:20.41,Default,It would be more than an\Nequally elastic rebound.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.81,0:54:22.05,Default,So we're going to\Nmake it so we can set
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.05,0:54:24.08,Default,that elasticity anywhere\Nfrom zero to one.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.40,0:54:27.80,Default,Okay? Zero would mean just kind\Nof hits and dampens immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.50,0:54:29.33,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.37,0:54:31.22,Default,So let's go get Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.49,0:54:34.25,Default,Bouncer. Here's Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.95,0:54:40.26,Default,Okay. Bouncer has not changed\Nsince last it was posted.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.63,0:54:44.75,Default,The elasticity is here, this\Nelastic, dynamic behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.75,0:54:46.74,Default,And you can see that\Nwe set it to one,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.26,0:54:48.84,Default,okay, by default right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.23,0:54:51.38,Default,So we want to be able\Nto set this elasticity
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.67,0:54:54.30,Default,from the settings app.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.30,0:54:57.16,Default,So let's build the UI for it\Nfirst, and then we'll have
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.16,0:54:59.97,Default,to change our code to\Nuse the NS user default
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.97,0:55:01.25,Default,that our UI's going to set.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.65,0:55:06.37,Default,So to do the UI we just do new\Nfile, go to the resource section
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.37,0:55:08.87,Default,of iOS, settings bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.02,0:55:11.26,Default,Same place we did strings file\Nright here, settings bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.63,0:55:12.89,Default,Create the settings bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.42,0:55:15.00,Default,You can call the bundle\Nwhatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.00,0:55:15.83,Default,Doesn't really matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.83,0:55:17.04,Default,I'm going to call it settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.05,0:55:19.24,Default,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.24,0:55:20.43,Default,Here's the settings bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.73,0:55:25.02,Default,And this root dot P list\Nis what the bundle is,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.02,0:55:26.76,Default,and you can see it\Nhas four items here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.02,0:55:30.87,Default,Again, group, text field,\Ntoggle switch, slider.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.64,0:55:34.79,Default,Okay? So you get this --
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.79,0:55:36.93,Default,every time you create a settings\Nbundle you get this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.93,0:55:38.33,Default,Let's go ahead and see\Nwhat this looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.67,0:55:41.41,Default,Let's do this over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.52,0:55:50.18,Default,[ Pause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.68,0:55:55.04,Default,So here's our Bouncer, and you\Ncan see it's got full elasticity
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.23,0:55:56.81,Default,-- bounces pretty good, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.48,0:56:00.22,Default,And if we go over to the\Nsettings app right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.78,0:56:03.96,Default,if we scroll down to the bottom,\Nyou'll see that in addition
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.96,0:56:05.62,Default,to these other apps,\Nthere's Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.77,0:56:07.39,Default,Okay? If Bouncer\Nhad a nice icon,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.39,0:56:08.33,Default,the icon would look better.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.33,0:56:10.59,Default,But if we click on\NBouncer, here's the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.73,0:56:14.46,Default,So we got this slider right\Nhere that we can move around
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.46,0:56:15.87,Default,and we've got the\Nswitch to turn off.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.94,0:56:18.40,Default,But none of this is connected\Nto Bouncer in any way;
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.40,0:56:20.73,Default,this is just the\Ndefault stuff we got
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.76,0:56:22.15,Default,from creating the settings app.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.15,0:56:24.65,Default,So what I'm going to do is\NI'm going to keep the slider,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.73,0:56:27.06,Default,and I'm going to have the\Nslider go from zero to one --
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.20,0:56:28.57,Default,elasticity zero to one.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.95,0:56:31.16,Default,I'm going to get rid of this\Nenabled switch right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.16,0:56:34.32,Default,I'm going to get rid of this\Nname text field right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.32,0:56:36.73,Default,And I'm going to keep the\Ngroup, but instead of calling it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.73,0:56:38.34,Default,"group," I'm going to\Ncall it "elasticity."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.34,0:56:40.39,Default,So I'm going to have this\Nreally simple UI here
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.39,0:56:42.20,Default,that says elasticity\Nand then has a slider.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.85,0:56:43.16,Default,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.72,0:56:44.93,Default,So let's go here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.09,0:56:47.48,Default,Let's get rid of\Nthis text field.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.98,0:56:50.39,Default,Let's get rid of\Nthis toggle switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.88,0:56:53.01,Default,And so I'm keeping the\Ngroup and the slider.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.01,0:56:57.55,Default,I'm going to rename the group\Nfrom group to be "elasticity."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.03,0:57:01.48,Default,And then in my slider let's look\Nat some of these things here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.74,0:57:03.36,Default,Okay, the maximum value is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.55,0:57:04.15,Default,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.43,0:57:06.02,Default,Okay? That's maximum\Nelasticity I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.10,0:57:06.92,Default,Minimum zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.92,0:57:07.48,Default,So that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.48,0:57:08.60,Default,I don't need to change that,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.60,0:57:10.35,Default,but you can obviously\Nchange these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.84,0:57:15.08,Default,The default value of .5 -- no,\NI really want my default value
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.08,0:57:18.08,Default,to be one because that's what\Nmy default value was before,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.08,0:57:19.43,Default,and I want it to start there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.29,0:57:22.66,Default,And then this is very\Nimportant, slider preference.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.66,0:57:25.18,Default,This is going to be\Nthe NS user default
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.45,0:57:26.73,Default,that communicates this back.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.73,0:57:30.65,Default,And I'm going to call this\Nsettings underbar elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.57,0:57:34.46,Default,Okay? When I do the names\Nof NS user defaults,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.55,0:57:38.45,Default,I like to name scope them,\Nlike, with the name of the class
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.50,0:57:42.06,Default,and then an underbar and\Nthen all the items in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.06,0:57:44.65,Default,So you kind of give it a\Nlittle bit of protection
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.65,0:57:46.29,Default,against the same name thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.67,0:57:48.42,Default,Here, since this\Nis set in settings,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.42,0:57:50.25,Default,I'm going to scope\Nit to be settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.71,0:57:53.85,Default,Okay? We could argue there\Nare better ways to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.85,0:57:55.21,Default,But it's a simple way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.21,0:57:56.40,Default,So this is going to be the name
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.40,0:57:58.17,Default,of the NS user default\Nwe want in our code.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.52,0:58:00.57,Default,So now let's go back\Nto our code and use
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.57,0:58:03.38,Default,that NS user default\Ninstead of 1.0 here.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.38,0:58:04.84,Default,So I'm going to get\Nrid of this 1.0.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.10,0:58:06.36,Default,And in fact, I'm\Ngoing to add a method
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.36,0:58:08.63,Default,to do this called\Nreset elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.19,0:58:11.83,Default,And let's write that method.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.27,0:58:14.95,Default,Oops. Void.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.83,0:58:17.61,Default,Reset elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.32,0:58:24.29,Default,And here I'm going to get the\Nuser default right off the bat
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.29,0:58:25.17,Default,-- NS user default.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.17,0:58:26.20,Default,You know how to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.20,0:58:30.29,Default,Defaults. Standard user\Ndefaults, value for key.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.91,0:58:33.89,Default,And the key is settings,\Nelasticity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.19,0:58:35.23,Default,Okay? Again, probably want
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.23,0:58:37.00,Default,to pound sign define\Nthere, whatever, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.03,0:58:38.55,Default,But for demo we'll go here.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.07,0:58:40.33,Default,I'm going to say if it's set --
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.02,0:58:42.76,Default,because it might be that\Nthat's never been set;
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.90,0:58:46.51,Default,no one's ever gone to the\Nsettings app and set this
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.51,0:58:47.71,Default,so it might just\Nnot even be set.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.14,0:58:52.00,Default,So if it's set, then I'll do\None thing; if it's not set,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.00,0:58:54.39,Default,if no one's ever gone into\Nsettings, then I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.39,0:58:58.89,Default,to set my elasticity to be 1.0,\Nwhich is what it was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.44,0:59:01.82,Default,But if someone has gone to the\Nsettings app, then I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.82,0:59:07.51,Default,to set my elasticity to be\Nthis elasticity's float value.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.65,0:59:11.11,Default,Simple as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.07,0:59:16.44,Default,Okay? Now, this works\Ngreat the first time we ask
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.44,0:59:17.46,Default,for the elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.46,0:59:21.30,Default,But what if someone goes over to\Nsettings while my app is running
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.30,0:59:22.64,Default,and changes the elasticity?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.23,0:59:25.14,Default,Okay? We need to\Nfind out about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.31,0:59:27.19,Default,and we do that with\Na radio station.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.57,0:59:30.09,Default,Okay? So we're going to listen\Nto another radio station.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.09,0:59:32.93,Default,We're already listening to two\Nradio stations in this app --
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.02,0:59:34.58,Default,the resign and become active.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.58,0:59:37.96,Default,So I'm just going to add another\Nradio station listener here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.25,0:59:40.08,Default,Notification center,\Ndefault center.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.94,0:59:43.93,Default,And then a little\NStar Wars there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.66,0:59:47.62,Default,And then we're going to\Nadd observer for name.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.76,0:59:49.57,Default,Okay? And this thing\Nwe're going to --
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.57,0:59:51.15,Default,radio station we're\Ngoing to observe --
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.40,0:59:55.32,Default,is called NS user defaults\Ndid change notification,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.32,0:59:58.04,Default,exactly what you would\Nthink it would be called.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.40,1:00:01.33,Default,Okay? And we don't\Ncare who is going
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.33,1:00:03.11,Default,to tell us that it changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.92,1:00:05.65,Default,And we can do it on this queue.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.65,1:00:06.26,Default,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.53,1:00:08.50,Default,And what are we going\Nto do when it changes?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.72,1:00:13.44,Default,Well, of course, we are just\Ngoing to reset the elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.06,1:00:17.67,Default,Okay? And that's why I put\Nthat in a separate method.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.67,1:00:23.07,Default,Okay? So it's going to call\Nthis, it's going to read
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.07,1:00:25.46,Default,that user default,\Nupdate the elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.46,1:00:29.86,Default,As we know with the dynamic\Nanimator, as soon as you change
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.86,1:00:32.88,Default,that elasticity, it's going
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.87,1:00:37.16,Default,to immediately start\Naffecting the elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.36,1:00:40.32,Default,Okay? So let's go\Nahead and try this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.62,1:00:41.58,Default,See if this works.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.52,1:00:47.00,Default,[ Pause ]
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.50,1:00:52.35,Default,>> For the slider,\Nwhats the granularity?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.35,1:00:53.86,Default,>> Yeah. So the question\Nis: What's the granularity
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.86,1:00:55.38,Default,of the slider as we move along?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.27,1:00:57.64,Default,And it depends.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.87,1:01:02.27,Default,If it's a float, then however\Nwide the slider is, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.27,1:01:04.43,Default,however many points that\Ncan be divided into,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.43,1:01:05.79,Default,that's how much granularity\Nyou're going
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.79,1:01:06.49,Default,to get on the float.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.49,1:01:09.57,Default,If it's an integer -- you know,\Nif you're making integer --
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.57,1:01:11.71,Default,then you're going to be rounding\Noff to the nearest integer,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.97,1:01:14.05,Default,right, as you get it\Nfrom NS user defaults.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.05,1:01:17.30,Default,But basically granularity\Ndepends on the width available.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.30,1:01:19.03,Default,So it's actually going\Nto vary per device.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.25,1:01:21.55,Default,Right? On a wide device you\Ncan get a higher granularity.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.41,1:01:22.96,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.96,1:01:25.57,Default,So here we are; elasticity\Nis default.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.37,1:01:28.77,Default,Okay? So -- oops.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.77,1:01:31.06,Default,This guy's hard to control.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.28,1:01:34.90,Default,Okay. So we had normal\Nelasticity going on here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.90,1:01:37.18,Default,So now I'm going to go\Nout to the settings app.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.32,1:01:39.92,Default,Okay? I'm going to\Ngo down to Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.92,1:01:41.33,Default,Here's Bouncer's elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.90,1:01:42.95,Default,It's at one.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.11,1:01:46.64,Default,I'm going to crank it\Nall the way down to zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.34,1:01:49.14,Default,Okay? Which is really\Nlow, it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.70,1:01:51.89,Default,And let's go back to Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.17,1:01:57.44,Default,And now when this thing\Nbounces, doesn't bounce.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.95,1:01:59.49,Default,Okay? Low elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.49,1:02:01.67,Default,Okay? Make sense?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.24,1:02:06.15,Default,And then we can go back again.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.89,1:02:09.78,Default,Change the elasticity\Nback to being high.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.49,1:02:13.34,Default,Back here to Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.89,1:02:16.35,Default,And now back to bouncing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.38,1:02:21.47,Default,Okay? Make sense\Nwhat we did there?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.01,1:02:23.26,Default,Now, one last thing\NI want to show you
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.26,1:02:24.82,Default,about this is localization.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.10,1:02:30.31,Default,So here we have settings\Nelasticity.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.31,1:02:32.67,Default,Well, that's correct\Nbecause we're in English.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.67,1:02:35.02,Default,But what happens if we go\Nand change the language here?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.08,1:02:47.84,Default,So let's go change to French --\Ninternational, language, French.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.74,1:02:49.59,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.59,1:02:52.19,Default,So now when we go back\Nto settings and we go
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.19,1:02:53.40,Default,down to look at Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.63,1:02:55.85,Default,Okay? So we go back here
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.85,1:02:57.79,Default,and it still says\Nelasticity even though I'm
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.79,1:02:58.54,Default,in French right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.54,1:03:00.00,Default,So this is all in French.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.30,1:03:02.51,Default,Okay? So we got this all in\NFrench -- nice, excellent,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.51,1:03:04.89,Default,all in French, except\Nfor Bouncer is English.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.19,1:03:08.08,Default,Okay? So this person is\Nimmediately deleting Bouncer,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.38,1:03:09.98,Default,this French person\Ndeleting Bouncer
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.98,1:03:11.32,Default,because of the English bias.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.81,1:03:13.20,Default,So how do we fix that?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.43,1:03:14.35,Default,Well, we go down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.35,1:03:17.68,Default,We want to change this\Nroot dot strings right here
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.74,1:03:23.26,Default,to say elasticity\Nequals elasticity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.43,1:03:25.52,Default,So this is what we\Nwould want in English.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.68,1:03:27.53,Default,And in French we'd want\Nthis to be the French word,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.53,1:03:28.66,Default,or the dots, or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.02,1:03:30.90,Default,So how are we going to do this?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.90,1:03:32.25,Default,And this is where we have to go
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.25,1:03:34.71,Default,out to the file system\Nand do this manually.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.99,1:03:38.10,Default,So the way you can go out to the\Nfile system is you select the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.10,1:03:39.79,Default,settings bundle,\Nright-click on it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.35,1:03:43.36,Default,and you can see the very first\Nthing here is show in finder.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.78,1:03:44.60,Default,So I'll show in finder.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.60,1:03:47.63,Default,Here it is, but it doesn't\Nhave a little triangle.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.63,1:03:49.14,Default,That's because it's a package.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.52,1:03:52.95,Default,Okay? But I can right-click\Nand say show package contents.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.49,1:03:55.16,Default,Now it will show me\Nwhat's inside of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.47,1:03:57.03,Default,Here's my EN dot lproj.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.03,1:03:59.06,Default,I'm just going to\Ncopy it and paste it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.37,1:04:01.40,Default,So now I have EN dot lproj two.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.89,1:04:07.07,Default,So I'm going to rename\Nthis to be FR dot lproj.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.34,1:04:08.67,Default,What's really kind\Nof interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.67,1:04:10.23,Default,about the way the finder works
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.23,1:04:13.41,Default,with apps is this will\Nall be appearing in Xcode
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.41,1:04:14.81,Default,at the same time that\Nyou're typing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.92,1:04:17.24,Default,So you don't have to do\Nanything special there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.24,1:04:19.59,Default,As you create these\Ndirectories and rename them,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.59,1:04:21.86,Default,Xcode keeps track of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.86,1:04:23.92,Default,So here's the root\Ndot strings for French
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.92,1:04:25.01,Default,and here's the one for English.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.26,1:04:28.00,Default,So in the French one let's\Nchange this to our dot.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.03,1:04:32.58,Default,Okay? Oops, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.58,1:04:35.44,Default,I wanna make sure\Nthis is...okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.82,1:04:40.55,Default,So we change this to the dots.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.55,1:04:43.90,Default,And now let's -- yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.00,1:04:46.09,Default,So now let's run this.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.00,1:04:52.02,Default,Reinstall this Bouncer,\Nincluding its settings bundle.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.55,1:04:53.07,Default,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.07,1:04:54.40,Default,So here we have Bouncer.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.40,1:04:59.15,Default,Let's go over to settings,\Nlook at Bouncer settings,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.15,1:05:01.81,Default,and now we have elasticity\Nwith the dots.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.62,1:05:04.89,Default,Okay? All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.24,1:05:06.78,Default,Questions about any of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.78,1:05:06.93,Default,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.32,1:05:10.65,Default,>> If you have settings in your\Napp that are frequently used,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.65,1:05:12.37,Default,should you refrain\Nfrom also putting them
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.64,1:05:14.98,Default,in this [inaudible] settings?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.05,1:05:15.66,Default,>> What a great question.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.66,1:05:18.40,Default,Okay. So the question is:\NIf I have settings in my app
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.99,1:05:22.13,Default,and the user frequently\Nwants to change them,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.13,1:05:25.03,Default,like let's say elasticity\Nis something that, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.03,1:05:27.38,Default,every game you want to play\Nwith a different elasticity
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.38,1:05:30.52,Default,or something like that because,\Nyou know, it's not something
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.52,1:05:32.19,Default,that you just kind\Nof set to taste
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.19,1:05:34.62,Default,and then you just leave\Nit, then you would not want
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.62,1:05:35.78,Default,to use the settings app.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.39,1:05:40.32,Default,Okay? Settings that the user\Nwants to set on a regular basis,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.32,1:05:41.91,Default,that are a normal\Npart the operation,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.91,1:05:43.96,Default,those want to be in your app.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.05,1:05:48.17,Default,So we would want to have some\Nway here in Bouncer to be able
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.17,1:05:51.35,Default,to set the elasticity -- maybe\Na gesture, maybe, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.41,1:05:52.54,Default,we're not using pinching.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.54,1:05:54.22,Default,Maybe pinching could\Ndo it or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.22,1:05:55.37,Default,I mean, if it's something\Nyou want
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.37,1:05:57.05,Default,to change a lot,\Nyou want it here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.27,1:05:59.24,Default,Okay? Or you have a\Ntitle bar across the top
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.24,1:06:00.99,Default,and have a bar button\Nfor it or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.39,1:06:03.18,Default,Really, the settings\Napp is set it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.18,1:06:05.58,Default,and forget it kind of settings.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.70,1:06:09.62,Default,Right? Settings that are just\Nmaybe something a user tunes
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.62,1:06:11.38,Default,that they like and\Nthen it's set.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.84,1:06:14.28,Default,Okay? It's not going\Nto be things
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.28,1:06:16.37,Default,that you're going\Nto set constantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.80,1:06:17.16,Default,Question?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.35,1:06:20.05,Default,>> Suppose that you did have\Na way to set them in your app,
