Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.52,1:06:38.32,Default,with every game.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.56,1:06:39.98,Default,Like, you say new\Ngame and it says,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.98,1:06:41.06,Default,"What elasticity do you want?"
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.42,1:06:42.54,Default,It's possible you might want
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.54,1:06:45.70,Default,to have setting apps set the\Ndefault elasticity, right,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.80,1:06:48.17,Default,so that when it asks you\Nabout the elasticity,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.17,1:06:49.43,Default,it starts with that default.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.73,1:06:51.28,Default,So it's possible you\Nmight want to have that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.58,1:06:53.84,Default,But generally you don't want\Nthe user confused about,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.84,1:06:54.95,Default,"Where am I setting this?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.95,1:06:56.76,Default,Am I setting it in settings,\Nor am I setting it here?"
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.07,1:06:59.70,Default,So even in that case in\Nsettings you'd probably want
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.70,1:07:01.20,Default,to call it default elasticity,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.20,1:07:03.38,Default,and then here you would\Ncall it elasticity
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.38,1:07:03.99,Default,or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.83,1:07:05.71,Default,So good questions.
